    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Art not thou our God,.... In a peculiar sense, not merely as the Creator and Governor of men, but in a covenant relation their covenant God and Father: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who didst drive out the inhabitants of the land before thy people Israel; the seven nations of Canaan, to make way and room for Israel: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and gavest it to the seed of Abraham thy friend for ever? made a deed of gift of it to them, and settled it on them till the coming of the Messiah, and that as an instance of love and friendship to Abraham; and wilt thou therefore suffer it to be taken from his seed? ",
        "children": [
